{
  "texts": [
    "However, the cost in time and resources of retraining models from scratch makes this option unattractive in the short term, especially if forgetting requests have to be executed urgently.",
    "Privacy-preserving model pre-training.",
    "Using privacy-preserving ML mechanisms may limit the influence of any single data point on the model.",
    "In this case, instead of protecting the data, we use some training mechanism that ensures privacy.",
    "Mechanisms such as differentially private stochastic gradient descent (DP-SGD) (Abadi et al 2016) and private aggregation of teacher ensembles (PATE) (Papernot et al 2018) have been used in the last years to train privacy-preserving machine learning models."
  ]
}